17 mathematics after the beginning-of-the-year screening instrument,
18 shall be screened for dyscalculia. Screening also may be requested
19 for a student by his or her parent or legal guardian, teacher, or
20 counselor. A student who is identified with characteristics of
21 dyscalculia shall not be required to be rescreened unless requested
22 by his or her parent or legal guardian. Nothing in this section
23 shall preclude a school district from administering a dyscalculia
24 screening tool to identify, refer, evaluate, or provide appropriate
Req. No. 3832 Page 25

1 serv ices to any student suspected of having dyscalculia or another
2 math-related disorder prior to the 2027-2028 school year.
3 B. No later than December 31, 2025 February 28, 2027, the State
4 Board of Education, in consultation with the Office of Mathematics
5 Improvement within the State Department of Education, shall develop
6 policies for dyscalculia screening required pursuant to this section
7 and shall include, but not be limited to:
8 1. The definition and characteristics of dyscalculia and
9 related disorders;
10 2. The process for referring students in grades two through
11 five for screening;
12 3. A process for providing notification to parents or legal
13 guardians of the use of a qualified dyscalculia-screening
14 dyscalculia screening tool and notification of the results of the
15 screening;
16 4. A process for providing the parents or legal guardians of
17 students screened for dyscalculia with information and resource
18 material regarding dyscalculia;
19 5. A process for monitoring the student’s progress after the
20 positive identification of characteristics of dyscalculia or other
21 math-related disorders; and
22 6. Requirements and qualifications for screeners that
23 demonstrate an understanding of and training to administer the
24 screening instrument.
Req. No. 3832 Page 26

1 C. The Board shall adopt a list of approved qualified
2 dyscalculia screening tools based on recommendations from the Office
3 of Mathematics Improvement within the State Department of Education
4 that address developmentally appropriate components.
5 D. Screening shall be conducted in accordance with the policies
6 developed by the State Board of Education pursuant to subsection B
7 of this section and the guidance within the dyslexia and dysgraphia
8 handbook developed pursuant to Section 1210.517 of Title 70 of the
9 Oklahoma Statutes this title including policies and information
10 developed relating to universal screening of students for
11 characteristics of dyscalculia.
12 E. Beginning June 30, 2026 June 30, 2028, and June 30 each year
13 thereafter, public school districts shall provide the following data
14 to the State Department of Education:
15 1. The number of students by grade level in grades two through
16 five who were screened for dyscalculia in a school year;
17 2. The number of students by grade level in grades two through
18 five who were newly identified as having characteristics of
19 dyscalculia in a school year;
20 3. The process or tools used to evaluate student progress;
21 4. The number of trained school system personnel or licensed
22 professionals used to administer the qualified dyscalculia screening
23 tool;
24
Req. No. 3832 Page 27

1 5. The number of students in grades two through five who were
2 participating in interventions within the school setting and the
3 number of students participating in interventions outside the school
4 setting; and
5 6. The programs used by districts for intervention within the
6 school setting.
7 F. The State Department of Education shall designate personnel
8 to provide technical assistance to implement the provisions of this
9 act the Oklahoma Math Achievement and Proficiency Act.
10 G. By December 31, 2026 December 31, 2028, and by December 31
11 each year thereafter, the State Department of Education shall
12 electronically provide a report containing all of the data provided
13 pursuant to subsection E of this section to the Governor and
14 Legislature and make the report available on the Department’s
15 website.
16 H. As funds are available, beginning with the 2026-2027 school
17 year, the Department shall provide training on the best practices
18 for screening for dyscalculia.
19 I. The State Board of Education may promulgate rules to
20 implement the provisions of this section.
